{"content":"## Remix Themes\nRemix themes is a slick way to handle themes in your Remix app. Read more about it [here](https://github.com/abereghici/remix-themes).\n<Installation options={{ isManual: true }}  items={['remix-themes']}/>\n\n## Session Storage\nAnd next, in your `app/sessions.server.tsx` file, add the following:\n<PlainCode code={`import { createCookieSessionStorage } from '@remix-run/node'\n  import { createThemeSessionResolver } from 'remix-themes'\n\n  const isProduction = process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'\n\n  const sessionStorage = createCookieSessionStorage({\n    cookie: {\n      name: 'theme',\n      path: '/',\n      httpOnly: true,\n      sameSite: 'lax',\n      secrets: ['s3cr3t'],\n      ...(isProduction ? { domain: 'your-production-domain.com', secure: true } : {})\n    }\n  })\n\n  export const themeSessionResolver = createThemeSessionResolver(sessionStorage)`} />\n\n## Providers\nNext to add the `ThemeProvider` to your root layout like so:\n```\nexport { Theme, useTheme } from 'remix-themes'\n```\n\n## Action Route\nCreate a file in `/routes/action.set-theme.ts`. Make sure you pass the filename to the `ThemeProvider` component. This route stores the preferred theme in session storage when the user switches it up.\n\n```tsx\nimport { themeSessionResolver } from '@/sessions.server'\nimport { createThemeAction } from 'remix-themes'\n\nexport const action = createThemeAction(themeSessionResolver)\n```\n\n## Theme Switcher\nFor theme switcher, you can use the `useTheme` hook from `remix-themes` to get the current theme.\n<Installation options={{ isManual: true }}  items={['justd-icons']} />\nThen, make sure you import the icons you want to use.\n\n<PlainCode code={`import { Button } from 'ui'\n  import { IconMoon, IconSun } from 'justd-icons'\n  import { Theme, useTheme } from '@/components/theme-provider'\n\n  export function ThemeSwitcher() {\n    const [theme, setTheme] = useTheme()\n    const switchTheme = () => {\n      if (theme === 'dark') {\n        setTheme(Theme.LIGHT)\n      } else {\n        setTheme(Theme.DARK)\n      }\n    }\n\n    return (\n      <Button\n        appearance=\"outline\"\n        size=\"square-petite\"\n        aria-label=\"Switch theme\"\n        onPress={switchTheme}\n      >\n        <IconSun className=\"h-[1.2rem] w-[1.2rem] rotate-0 scale-100 transition-all dark:-rotate-90 dark:scale-0\" />\n        <IconMoon className=\"absolute h-[1.2rem] w-[1.2rem] rotate-90 scale-0 transition-all dark:rotate-0 dark:scale-100\" />\n      </Button>\n    )\n  }`} />\n\nIf you spot typos or wrong implementations, feel free to [contribute here](https://github.com/irsyadadl/d./blob/main/content/docs/dark-mode/remix.mdx).","title":"Remix","description":"Ready to remix your project with some dark mode flair? Dive into this guide and get your app groovinâ€™ in the dark.","_meta":{"filePath":"dark-mode/remix.mdx","fileName":"remix.mdx","directory":"dark-mode","extension":"mdx","path":"dark-mode/remix"},"toc":[{"title":"Remix Themes","url":"#remix-themes","depth":2},{"title":"Session Storage","url":"#session-storage","depth":2},{"title":"Providers","url":"#providers","depth":2},{"title":"Action Route","url":"#action-route","depth":2},{"title":"Theme Switcher","url":"#theme-switcher","depth":2}],"structuredData":{"contents":[{"heading":"remix-themes","content":"Remix themes is a slick way to handle themes in your Remix app. Read more about it here."},{"heading":"session-storage","content":"And next, in your app/sessions.server.tsx file, add the following:"},{"heading":"providers","content":"Next to add the ThemeProvider to your root layout like so:"},{"heading":"action-route","content":"Create a file in /routes/action.set-theme.ts. Make sure you pass the filename to the ThemeProvider component. This route stores the preferred theme in session storage when the user switches it up."},{"heading":"theme-switcher","content":"For theme switcher, you can use the useTheme hook from remix-themes t